AIM:

To write a C program to convert starting lowercase letter of each word into uppercase in given file.

ALGORITHM:

1.	Declare file descriptor, file descriptor 1, n as int.
2.	Initialize n as 99.
3.	Declare buf as char.
4.	In both file descriptor, open the file with different permission (Read and  Write).
5.	If file is empty, print error.
6.	Else print success and initialize n as 10.
a.	Read the file contents.	
7.	 Check each word starting character in a file, if it is in a lowercase letter or not.
8.	If it is in a lowercase letter then decrement the value by 32, changed to uppercase letter.
9.	Write the letter in a file as an uppercase letter.
10.	If it is in an uppercase, then write the letter in a file
11.	Check whether read contents is a space or new line, and then write as it is.
12.	Repeat from step 7 to 11 till while loop is true.

SOURCE CODE:

#include”head.h”
int main(int argc,char* argv[])
{
int fd,fd1,n=99;
char buf;
fd=open(argv[1],0);
fd1=open(argv[1],1);
if((fd==-1)|| (fd1==-1))
printf(“error\n”);
else
{
printf(“success\n”);
n=10;
read(fd,&buf,1);
if((buf>=’a’)&&(buf<=’z’))
{
buf=buf-32;
write(fd1,&buf,1);
}
else
write(fd1,&buf,1);
while(n>0)
{
n=read(fd,&buf,1);
if((buf==’’)&&(buf==’\n’))
{
write(fd1,&buf,1);
read(fd,&buf,1);
if((buf>=’a’)&&(buf<=’z’))
{
buf=buf-32;
write(fd1,&buf,1);
}
else
write(fd1,&buf,1);
} else
write(fd1,&buf,1);}}}

INPUT: 
./a.out file.txt

hello world

OUTPUT:

Success

Hello World

RESULT:

Thus, the C program converted the lowercase letter of each word into uppercase in given file.
